<br>
While at the higher levels or in &quot;better&quot; grouping situations there might be stacking problems, I've never had a stacking issue with Divine Vigor with /anyone/ I've cast it on, ever.<br>
<br>
I have 1455hp self-buffed without Symbol.  Divine Vigor provides almost 7% of my total hitpoints.  That means I can stay in combat 7% longer, be it beating down on a mob, taking hits so others can run, or getting beat on while I run.  100hp is significant to me - mobs around this level generally hit for 20-60hp, and sometimes (grimlings especially) they hit for &lt;10.  That 100 extra hp means about 2-4 extra successful hits I can stand, which often means many more rounds of combat (as mobs can often miss).<br>
<br>
Its like a Symbol, except its reagentless and stacks with the symbol line.  Have you _never_ used one of our own Symbols?  Sure, most of the time the extra 50hp from our first symbol isn't worth the 2gp for the reagent, but haven't you ever used one, just when you thought it was going to be a tough fight ahead and wanted to be a little safer?  Divine Vigor is just a _free_ Symbol that you can use.  I used our lvl 30 symbol about 6 times in 9 levels, and I've never used our 39 one - but I used Divine Vigor constantly, because 100hp is very significant to me.<br>
<br>
Additionally, in a grouped situation, its a free 100hp for the lighter classes.  While it may only be an extra 1 or 2 hits for the lightly armored casters, it still that much longer for them to live if things go bad.<br>
<br>
Thinking about it another way, Daring is ~100hp.  Would you go choose to not use your Center-line spell?<br>
<br>
I don't mean this as a flame.  We each have our own playstyles and opinions.  I just find this an extremely useful spell.  I would dread a nerf of it, but if it happens, oh well.<br>
Dunthor Warsmith <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uluthair.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Luthair</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1676<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/11/02 6:05:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14452.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rule of Unintended Consequences</span><hr size=1> When you aren't getting chealed it doesn't really matter how many HP you have.  (Obviously you need enough to survive and avoid agro)  Solo the only HP buff I use is Daring from helm.<br>
