<br>
No, I'd use it.  And I'd use Divine Vigor if it were 50hp.  I'll use every tool at my disposal.<br>
<br>
Similarly, I want all my tools <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> to work</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.  I want to have spells that are worth scribing and memming.  They won't all be that way, and I understand that.  Do you expect me at level 53 to keep using the spell I got at level 39, rather than question its true intent?  Should I sit back and accept two spells that aren't worth the digital paper they're scribbled on?<br>
<br>
I think it was best said:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> it feels just as gimp at 39 as DG does at 53, and DS at 60<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Take the dismay you feel at possibly losing that 50 hit points.  Now multiply that times 2 hell levels (40 &amp; 45), then add the hell levels of 51, 52, and 53.  Realize that at 53 the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> only</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> spell you get is the one that is dwarfed by your level 39 spell.  And that spell follows such heavyweights as resist disease, pacify, and frenzied strength.<br>
<br>
Hard as it may be to believe, most of us in the 50's fought through the 40's without Divine Vigor, Instrument of Nife, and Valor of Marr.  We appreciate those spells, but if one of the higher level spells needs adjusting, I'll continue to bring it up.<br>
